# UI guidelines (AgenticVerdict)

Before adding or changing user-facing UI, use these sources of truth:

- **Design system overview:** `/design/README.md`
- **Pencil / generation workflows:** `/design/docs/generation/ui-generation-quick-reference.md`
- **Full design docs:** `/design/docs/`

## Rules

1. **`.pen` files** — Create and edit only with **Pencil MCP** tools (`batch_get`, `batch_design`, etc.). Do not hand-edit `.pen` JSON except when fixing validator-approved mechanical issues.
2. **MCP-first UI implementation** — Pencil MCP does not write `.tsx` files. Before changing user-facing UI for a `.pen`-backed screen: inspect the design with MCP (`get_editor_state`, `batch_get`, `get_variables`, `get_screenshot`), load **`get_guidelines({ category: "guide", name: "Code" })`** and **`get_guidelines({ category: "guide", name: "Tailwind" })`** when using Tailwind, then implement using MCP-sourced values (see `/design/docs/generation/ui-generation-cheatsheet.md#mcp-first-design-to-code-workflow-repo-ssot`). Do not invent colors/spacing from memory.
3. **React / Mantine** — Implement screens using **`@agenticverdict/ui`** and Mantine v9 patterns already in the repo; align with atoms/molecules specs and design tokens (no one-off duplicate components).
4. **Accessibility** — Target **WCAG 2.1 AA** (contrast, focus, keyboard, labels).
5. **Localization** — Support **RTL and LTR** via logical properties and tenant/theme config (`CompanyConfig`), not hardcoded direction.
6. **Pre-flight** — Check `/design/README.md` for an existing pattern; run `pnpm run validate:pen-files` after `.pen` changes.

See also: `/prompts/ui-guidelines-enforcement.md`, `/design/ENFORCEMENT-GAP-ANALYSIS.md`.
